---
import Base from "../../layouts/Base.astro";
import Lead from "../../components/Lead.astro";
import StepNav from "../../components/StepNav.astro";
import NoticeAside from "../../components/NoticeAside.astro";
---

<Base
  title="States shift all day"
  description="Step three: these states move through a normal day all the time — noticing the shifts is the first skill."
  crumbs={[
    { label: "start here", href: "start/" },
  ]}
>
  <h1 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl">States shift all day. That's normal.</h1>
  <Lead>
    A nervous system in good shape doesn't stay calm all the time — it
    <em>moves</em>. Something startles you, you rev up; it passes, you settle.
    You get absorbed in something, you brighten; you tire, you dim. The states
    are supposed to shift. Flexibility is the health, not permanent calm.
  </Lead>

  <div class="prose">
    <p>
      Think of an ordinary morning. The alarm jolts you (a little activation).
      Coffee and quiet settle you. A tense email spikes you. A walk outside
      brings you back down. None of that is a problem — it's a nervous system
      doing exactly its job, rising and falling with the day.
    </p>
    <p>
      Trouble looks less like "having states" and more like <em>getting
      stuck</em> in one — staying revved long after the stressor is gone, or
      staying shut down when it would be safe to come back up. A lot of
      healing is simply widening the range again, so the system can move the
      way it's meant to.
    </p>
    <p>
      And the very first skill is small: just noticing which way the weather is
      blowing, without needing to fix it.
    </p>
  </div>

  <NoticeAside>
    <p class="m-0">
      There's a sound in the room with you right now that you'd stopped
      hearing — a fan, the fridge, traffic, the hum of the screen. It didn't
      get louder. Your attention just landed on it, because this sentence
      sent it there. That landing — that's noticing. It's the whole first
      skill, and you already have it. You can let the sound fade back now if
      you like.
    </p>
  </NoticeAside>

  <StepNav step={3} />
</Base>
